# Git Push Authentication

When the user asks to push, commit and push, or deploy via git push:

1. **Always use the GitHub PAT** from `.config/secrets.env` — the variable is `GITHUB_PAT_PANTERA_CLAWW_APP`
2. Source the secrets file and use the token in the push URL:

```bash
set -a && source .config/secrets.env && set +a && git push "https://${GITHUB_PAT_PANTERA_CLAWW_APP}@github.com/panterasan33/pantera-claw.git" main
```

3. Do not use plain `git push` — it will fail with "Repository not found" because the remote requires token authentication.
